'''New Years Eve 2026''' is the tenth annual [[New Years Eve]] event held by [[VRChat]]. Users celebrate the 2026 New Year in a medieval-themed version world.

==Background==
On November 13th 2025, VRChat announced that content submissions for the 2026 New Years world would open on November 17th, 2025. Confirming the event would return for it's tenth year.<ref>[https://x.com/VRChat/status/1989092253089091886 NYE2026 Submissions Announcement]</ref>

Included in the announcement, VRChat shared the type of submissions users can submit, along with guidelines<ref>[https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vQT-vHYBv3pzKT2CHDLiajezkmvpuF5H6FpxL65_UcXxd2mw1CXDdrWVSKZ5AuDQFos5YDW1eNX_KdE/pub NYE2026 Submissions Guidelines]</ref> to follow for submissions to be accepted. The type of submissions users can submit are Posters, Booths, Graffiti, and videos for the VRChat Entertainment Network. The deadline for submissions was on December 10th, 2025.

==Shop & Content Drop==
Two days before the New Year's world release, VRChat released the "[[List of Shop listings#New Year's Celebration|New Year's Celebration]]" shelf into the [[Shop]], as well as the "New Year's 2026 Bundle" as a VRC+ content drop. 

The Shop contains the "NYE Celebratory Bundle", which contains 5 items, 3 stickers, 2 premium emoji, 1 portal, and 1 warp effect, themed around New Years. The VRC+ content drop contains 2 items, and 1 warp effect.

==World==
[[File:NYE2026_World_Main.webp|thumb|The world from the back of spawn.]]
The world was released on December 31st, 2025, along with a world row. The world came with three separate versions, a [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_a560491e-6f55-4d13-a96f-cdbc34dd80f8 normal capacity], [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_e7ab0a1f-9a28-4165-8246-5eaf79972558 high capacity], and an [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_7c5561e1-5113-4a85-9e4e-d676daf5ff6b unlocked video player] version.

=== Posters, Booths, and Graffiti===
<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed">
Posters are scattered throughout the world which were submitted by the community. The world contains 138 posters.
<div class="mw-collapsible-content">{{:New Years Eve 2026 Posters}}</div>
</div>

[[File:NYE2026_World_Music_Alley_Graffiti.webp|thumb|Graffiti located in the Music Alley.]]
In addition to the posters, there are booths located down the main strip and graffiti in the alley. There are 18 community booths, 2 VRChat booths, and countless graffiti.

=== Entertainment Network ===
During the event, VRChat streamed the Entertainment Network on their Twitch stream which was also displayed in the low, high capacity versions of the world. It contained 13 hours+ of footage.<ref>"Did you submit a video to the VRChat Entertainment Network?...", https://x.com/VRChat/status/2006111019064562049</ref> 

The video files were available to download from January 6 - Feb 2026. They can be viewed on the Internet Archive [https://archive.org/details/vrchat-entertainment-network-nye-2026 here].

<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed">
The schedule includes 244 videos submitted by the community.
<div class="mw-collapsible-content">{{Entertainment Network 2026 Schedule}}</div>
</div>

=== Quest ===
[[File:NYE2026_World_Fish_Shop.webp|thumb|The Fish Shop.]]
Users can find cheese which are scattered throughout the world. There are 50 cheeses to collect, and progress can be viewed at the "Fish Shop" booth located behind the left ramp facing the ball drop from spawn.

